==English==
===Etymology===
[[blend|Blend]] of [[trust fund]] and [[Rastafarian]]
[[Category:Portmanteaus]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#Trustafarian is a portmanteau made from the words trust–fund and Rastafarian. If is used to describe and characterise some white people who adopt the manners of a specific black sub culture (Rastafarianism) in other circumstances they are called wiggers. They are people, often young to middle aged, who fuse the fashion sensibilities of a hippie with that of a Rastafarian. They often subscribe to an unemployed, shiftless life of hedonism based upon an unlimited amount of funds (a trust fund). In some cases they adopt a self-restrictive attitude to some forms of consumption based on their understanding of Rastafarianism to which they see them selves subscribing. This is often adapted cutting out chicken as well as the pork avoided by Rastafarians into a vegan diet.

